1)What are arithmetic operators in Java?
-->👉 Arithmetic operators are used to perform mathematical operations.
  🔹 Operators:
  + → Addition
  - → Subtraction
  * → Multiplication
  / → Division
  % → Modulus (remainder)
  Example:
  int a = 10, b = 3;
  
  System.out.println(a + b); // 13
  System.out.println(a - b); // 7
  System.out.println(a * b); // 30
  System.out.println(a / b); // 3
  System.out.println(a % b); // 1


2)What happens when we divide numbers of different types in Java (int and float)?
For example:
int / int
float / int
int / float
float / float
-->👉 Java follows type promotion (converts to bigger type)
        🔹 Cases:
        ✅ int / int
        int a = 5, b = 2;
        System.out.println(a / b); // 2
        👉 Integer division → decimal removed
        ✅ float / int
        float a = 5.0f;
        int b = 2;
        System.out.println(a / b); // 2.5
        👉 Result is float
        ✅ int / float
        int a = 5;
        float b = 2.0f;
        System.out.println(a / b); // 2.5
        👉 Result is float
        ✅ float / float
        float a = 5.0f, b = 2.0f;
        System.out.println(a / b); // 2.5
        👉 Result is float
        🔥 Rule:
        👉 If any one operand is float/double → result is floating-point



3)What happens when you divide by zero using integer division?
-->Division by zero (integer)
    int a = 10 / 0;
    👉 ❌ Throws:
    ArithmeticException: / by zero
    🔹 But with float:
    System.out.println(10.0 / 0); // Infinity
    👉 ✔️ No error → gives Infinity


4)What is the difference between / and % operators?
-->
| Operator | Meaning             | Example      |
| -------- | ------------------- | ------------ |
| `/`      | Division (quotient) | `10 / 3 = 3` |
| `%`      | Remainder           | `10 % 3 = 1` |

int a = 10, b = 3;

System.out.println(a / b); // 3
System.out.println(a % b); // 1




5)Can arithmetic operators be overloaded in Java?
-->👉 ❌ No (for user-defined classes)
    🔹 Why?
    Java does not support operator overloading
    Except one case:
    👉 ✔️ + operator is overloaded for:
    Addition
    String concatenation
    Example:
    System.out.println(10 + 20);       // 30
    System.out.println("Hi " + "Java"); // Hi Java
